There will be a focus on how local residents are using innovation to tackle challenges within their communities. CAPE TOWN Western Cape MEC for Economic Opportunities Alan Winde will spend the next month visiting a variety of innovation centres in the province.There will be a focus on how local residents are using innovation to tackle challenges within their communities.These different development hubs also equip people with new skills to enhance their employability.Winde says they will also be tracking the success of users of these centres to determine whether the particular model should be rolled out in other communities.His trip kicked off at the ICAN Centre in Elsies River earlier on Tuesday.He said: From going and doing online courses and paid courses in the one space. But there s a recording studio where you can do sound and then you can also do robotics, and you can go and build robots and run them through app development programmes. There's also gaming programmes. 